storyInfo: La Pluma takes a vacation and returns to Dossoles. What she sees is a side of Dossoles different from what her brother saw.

attributes.content: No sense waiting, guapa. This weapon store is closed.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: Eh?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: You're a tourist, right? The store was pretty well known in Dossoles before. The owner always got a bunch of great wares that nobody else could ever get their hands on.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: Yeah, I know.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: But it's been a long time since it last opened for business.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: I know that, too.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Wow, I didn't expect you to know so much about Dossoles.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: But I'm sure there's one thing you didn't know.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: What is it?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Land is very valuable here in Dossoles, and this store is in an excellent location. Normally, it would have been rented out to another tenant long ago.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: But it's been almost a year since this store closed down, and it hasn't been rented out to everyone else.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: Do you know why?
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: This is no mere secret. Most common folk don't know about this. If you want to know, come buy a boutique from me, and I'll let you in on it. What do you say?
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: Because the owner and Mayor Candela have a close relationship.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: What, you know that too?
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: Of course I do.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Thief! C-Catch him!
attributes.name: Tourist

attributes.content: I'll go help out.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Her moves are light... Just like... una pluma.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: Heheh, nice haul today.
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: Stop right there.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Who are you?!
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: Hand back what you stole.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: And here I was wondering since when the pacos have been so efficient.
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: So it's just una chavala.
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: Little girl, did your parents ever tell you that playing hero here in Dossoles could get you killed...?
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: Before the criminal could finish his sentence, La Pluma had already advanced to the man and knocked his knife out of his hand.
Ahhhhhhh! My hand!
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: My mama died when I was still a kid, but both my fathers told me—
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: If you do bad things, you must answer for your crimes.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Hand over what you stole.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Ugh.
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: Huh...?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Don't think you're all that just because you've got moves, kid.
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: This is Dossoles. Lots of groups have their claws in here.
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: How do you know this whistle?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: This is a True Bolívarian signal.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Who exactly are you?!
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: I am... just a passerby.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Hmph, I don't care who you are, but you'll find out real soon you picked a fight with someone you shouldn't have...
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: I'm pretty sure I told you not to use this signal all the time.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Candela's people have their eyes on us.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Sorry, Boss, I ran into some trouble.
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: I almost got away, but this punk kid stopped me...
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: From Rhodes Island...?
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Tío Tacito.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Rafaela?
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Lower your weapon. She's one of us.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Rafaela... You mean, she's the Colonel's daughter?!
attributes.name: Criminal

attributes.content: Why, Tío?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Come with me, Rafaela. It's a long story.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Give back what you stole.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Will do.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: I thought you went to Rhodes Island with Ernesto. Why are you back?
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: I took some time off, and I thought I would come home to visit Papá.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Hahaha, I see.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: I don't know that man just now.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: He... He's one of my new lackeys. Of course you wouldn't know him.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Tío Tacito, I thought all of you left Dossoles a long time ago.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: A lot of us did leave after the Colonel was arrested... but he's old. Somebody has to take care of him, so a few of us stayed behind.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: You're lying, Tío.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I know you. The Tío I know would chew everyone out just for gambling on cards. You wouldn't let your subordinates do something like this.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: You say the thief's new, but he knows Papá's rank. You're lying. He's not new.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: And this room... It reeks of gunpowder.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: You're trying to put a team together to rescue him, aren't you?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: You dodged my grapple...? You've improved a lot.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Tío Barrow?!
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Sorry, Rafaela, but you can't go through here.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: You've gotten a lot smarter. You weren't this observant before.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: At first, I was just going to give you a warm welcome and let you be on your way.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: But you'll need to extend your vacation by a few days, I'm afraid.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: It's okay. I have plenty of paid time off saved up.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I didn't come to stop you guys, either.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I watched you grow up. If I had a daughter, I would hope she'd be a good girl like you.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: But now I can't let you go before we finish our goal.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Don't blame me for being so ruthless.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: You haven't been on our side ever since you and Ernesto left.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: What are you planning to do?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Nothing too different from before. Penetrate, ambush, demolish. Maybe slash Candela's face while we're at it.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Don't give me that 'isn't there some other way' kind of face like Ernesto, mija.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Did you know? José is dead.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Barrow!
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: She has a right to know. Am I wrong?
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: But that idiot didn't die in battle. He died because of his gambling.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Candela's a monster. The city she's built is a monster. We're no match for her.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Once we get the Colonel out of there, we're leaving this city.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Let me help.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: But you finally found such a good job. You don't have to get yourself involved.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: All you need to do is to stay here till we're done, and you can go free.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: But I can't just stand by and do nothing.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Enough, Tacito. How long are you going to keep that up?
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: She's a good girl, but she doesn't listen to anyone.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: She's our daughter! A daughter to every single one of us brothers!
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: I'm a Rhodes Islander. They won't be too hard on me. I'll help you make contact with Papá.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Look at how our daughter's grown.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: We're back.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Look. A fine fowlbeast.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: And I have the spices and other ingredients you wanted.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Thank you.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I cleaned up the kitchen, too. You can just leave the rest to me.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Alright. Us ruffians don't know how to cook. If you need anything, let us know.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Mhm.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I really need to hand it to you to come up with this roast fowlbeast idea. It's the colonel's favorite.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Fowlbeasts raised for food are usually heftier.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: We could write any messages we want to get to him on paper and stuff them inside, you bring it to the Colonel.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Maybe we can squeeze some trinkets in there, too.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Yeah, I want Papá to eat something that he likes, even if it's just once in a while.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: He probably hasn't had a good meal inside.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: ...Yeah.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: The Colonel has never been one to indulge in pleasures. He probably hasn't had a very good time in prison.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: He'll be so happy to have a taste of his daughter's roast fowlbeast.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: I'm sure he'll be delighted that you're worried about him. I mean...
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Barrow.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Fine, I won't bring it up.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Hermano... came back a while ago.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: He paid the colonel a visit and attended a wedding.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: I saw him from a distance. Didn't talk to him.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Do you hate him?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Hate him? No way.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: If it wasn't for him, all of us would probably have been buried in the wastes, back when the Colonel was arrested.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: He's got a bright future ahead of him. Maybe he'll actually become a successful man one day.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Tío Barrow, hand me that spice.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: You got it.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: As the flames grill the fowlbeast meat, a beautiful luster gradually appears.
Heh, this aroma sure brings me back.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Right... Before we came to Dossoles, we often grilled meat together out in the wilds.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: The kitchen utensils we had don't hold a candle to this stuff, we didn't have all these spices, we had to hunt for meat... It was terrible...
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: But as soon as we got the fire started and everyone started to gather around it, it felt like we could pull through even the harshest hardships.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: So it goes.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Tacito, catch.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: When did you buy this?
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Just now.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: How come I didn't notice?
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Do I even deserve to call myself a scout if you of all people notice me doing anything?
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Hmph.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: The bulky soldier doesn't rebuke. Instead, he simply cracks open a can of beer and chugs it.
I want one, too.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: You got it.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: La Pluma clumsily pulls the can's tab and holds it with both her hands, drinking its contents in small gulps.
The soldiers never cared much about their beer's quality, and its taste could not be more different from her brew.
But this exciting texture instantly reminds her of how things were before.
There was this one time after Papá won a battle, when everyone celebrated in the camp.
She had already learned how to cook by then, and she loved making food for them.
Hermano preferred quiet places, so he hid in the tent and tried to sleep.

But in the end, with all the noise around him, he had no choice but to come out and try to quiet them down, only for Papá to force him to join them as they drank. Both of them ended up completely hammered.
The camp was filled with cheers and laughter.
Back then, Papá often laughed out loud.
Back then, the things that worried Hermano were written all over his face.
The sizzling of the meat pulls her back to reality.
Suddenly, she is feeling a little thankful for the Doctor.
In the past, she would definitely be hung up on what she should do, and hope that someone would give her an idea.
But now, she knows what to do.
Ugh.
attributes.name: Tourist?

attributes.content: It's me.
attributes.name: Tourist?

attributes.content: Sorry, I lost her, but she's headed toward the prison. She's probably going to make contact with Pancho.
attributes.name: Tourist?

attributes.content: Yes, she made contact with what's left of Pancho's men.
attributes.name: Tourist?

attributes.content: Yeah, could very well be connected.
attributes.name: Tourist?

attributes.content: Assemble the men.
attributes.name: Tourist?

attributes.content: I really wish I could get a compliment from the Doctor at a time like this.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Papá, I'm here.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Oh, mija. You've finally come to visit.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: I brought you this, too. It's roast fowlbeast, your favorite.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Hoho, my own daughter's roast fowlbeast. It's been way too long.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: Come here and let me get a good look at you.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: Okay.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: You lost weight. Is the food at Rhodes Island that bad?
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: Not at all. It's very good.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Maybe it's because I've been out on missions a lot lately.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Don't overwork yourself. It's very important to sleep and eat on a regular schedule.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: Yeah, I know.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Papá, you have new scars.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Prison is a place where fists do the talking.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: All I did was tell a few men here that just because I'm getting on in years doesn't mean they can pick on me.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: I'll bring you some ointment next time.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Alright, alright.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: What do you think of Rhodes Island?
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: I think... it's a pretty good place. Everyone at the company's very friendly, and they treat us well.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: That's good to hear.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: But you can't settle down if you just keep working for them.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: Doesn't Rhodes Island travel to lots of different countries? You should look out when you go to all those different places with them.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: If you find somewhere that works for you, settle down there.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: Can't I come back to Bolívar?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Don't be silly, my daughter.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: There's nothing here in Bolívar. My greatest wish now is for you to live a peaceful life.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: What about Hermano?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: That malcriado...
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: He's got things he wants to do. Let him do them.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: With the ways things turned out, if he told me he wanted to be Candela's doorman, I'd let him.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: But he never thinks about what exactly it is that he wants to do.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: He's too hesitant and cautious. A man like him can't accomplish anything!
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: I... I'm sure he's aware.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: He knows what it is that he wants to do.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: He's just afraid.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Afraid? What could he even be afraid of?
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: He's afraid that if he really ended up picking a path, he'd lose you, and he'd lose me.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: ...Is that what you think?
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: He doesn't actually talk to me much aboard Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I think he probably thinks the same way as you do. He wants me to use Rhodes Island to find a place to settle down.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: But... why?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I grew up in Bolívar, too. How come I'm the only one who has to leave this place, and not either of you?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Because—
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: I was part of the rebellion.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I'm not innocent.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: You should never have been involved!
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: But I wasn't willing to just stand by and watch it all happen.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Besides... even if all I did was watch it happen... Does that really clear me of all involvement?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: The more I think about that, the more confused I am—
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: But at the same time, I also understand you and Hermano better and better.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I think I want to do something, too.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I made this roast fowlbeast with Tío Tacito and everyone else.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Tacito...
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: That bastard... Even if the situation is bad, he shouldn't have asked you to do this!
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: I wanted to.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I know that things are really complicated.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I'm trying to understand them, but I still don't grasp them completely.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: But there is one thing that I know.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: You can't let the people who respect you and look up to you to die for no reason.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: So... you don't want me to take this fowlbeast. Is that it?
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: ...Mhm.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Next time, I'll make you something even tastier.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: This is only the second time you've ever asked something of me.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: You've grown up, Rafaela.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: That's what you all say, but I don't think I'm much different from before.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I just want you to stay healthy and for Hermano to be more careful. It's that simple.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Ernesto came by a while back.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: Yeah, I know.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: He asked me if I remember what kind of flower his mother had clipped to her chest the first time we met.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: I told him I don't.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: I really don't.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: That also means... I'm old.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: It was a lilac.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: What? How did you...?
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: You told me.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: That day, she helped her inebriated father back to the tent, and in his haze, he started to talk.
As he continued, Papá began to cry.
He was remembering his wife.
The flower that she pinned to her chest when he first met her.
A lilac. A beautiful lilac.
Right, it was a lilac.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: How could I forget...?
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: Gracias, mija.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: Take this fowlbeast back with you.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: Are you sure?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Rafaela, mija.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: There are some things that I thought I'd only say to Ernesto. I never thought I'd have to say any of this to you, too.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: Once you've decided to do something, don't be a coward.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: And never let anyone influence your thinking.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: ...alright.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Papá?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: What is it?
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: If you told me what you told Hermano, then... will you tell him the same thing you told me?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Promise me.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I promise you.
attributes.name: Pancho

attributes.content: You ready?
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Thirty of us. Not one less.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Say, do you think Rafaela will come with?
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Don't be an idiot.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Who didn't want to drag her into this before?
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Hah, you're right about that.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Nothing good could come out of following a bunch of men who are doomed to die who-knows-where tomorrow.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: You want to die tomorrow?
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: If you ask me, I think today would do just fine.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Rafaela, you're back.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: How's the Colonel?
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: He's the same as he ever was.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Wait... Why did you bring the fowlbeast back out?
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: It's his choice.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Impossible.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: There's no way he's okay with dying in prison.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: You brat... you tricked us.
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: You talked him out of it, didn't you?
attributes.name: Shrewd Soldier

attributes.content: Candela's lackeys have been watching you the whole time.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I don't want you to get yourselves killed.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: You've always been so kind, mija.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: But I told you. We don't really have a lot of opportunities left.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: Out of the way.
attributes.name: Bulky Soldier

attributes.content: I won't let you through.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: The leader turns to his teammates behind him and nods to signal their impending attack.
This is a hideout of the remnants of Pancho's forces. Intelligence shows that they are planning to break Pancho out of prison.
Her orders are to kill every last one of them.
(Quietly) 3, 2, 1—
attributes.name: Candela's Subordinate

attributes.content: —Huh?
attributes.name: Candela's Subordinate

attributes.content: Candela's lackeys find themselves dumbfounded by what they see.
Inside the room, there are only a bunch of groaning soldiers on the ground and a girl standing in the middle.
She is holding a giant scythe. Its blade reflects a cold, awe-inspiring ray of light that lands on her face, revealing two dried up trails of tears.
What happened?
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Señora, they've been like this the moment we entered.
attributes.name: Candela's Subordinate

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: You're Ernesto's...
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: I'm an operator from Rhodes Island. Codename La Pluma.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: A Rhodes Island operator... What are you doing here?
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: I happened across these guerrillas hiding a stash of weapons, so I dealt with them.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: This is a Dossoles matter. You should have notified my subordinates as soon as you found them.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Sorry, Ms. Candela, but it was an emergency.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I'm sorry myself, that is not enough of a reason.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Before Candela can finish, her subordinates have already leveled their weapons on La Pluma.
Just then—
It's me.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: ...Ahah, I see. Very well. I'll be back soon.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: I've had a change of heart, my girl.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: This is a decent enough reason.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Take all of them back. Be good to them.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Ms. Candela?
attributes.name: Candela's Subordinate

attributes.content: An old friend of mine suddenly asked for a chat. I'm in a good mood.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Got it.
attributes.name: Candela's Subordinate

attributes.content: Come! We're picking up all this trash off the floor!
attributes.name: Candela's Subordinate

attributes.content: Yes, sir!
attributes.name: Candela's Subordinates

attributes.content: You're a brave one. You won a chance for them to live.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: What's on your mind now?
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: I'm wondering if I should thank you.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Hahaha.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Ernesto told me about his lovely, well-behaved sister. I didn't pay him any mind at the time, but now it seems his appraisal was biased.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: You know, my child? You should not have done this.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: What you should have done is watch it all happen, and then turn and leave.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: You are still young. You have the right to leave Bolívar.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: What you've done today might have saved a few men, but thanks to this, I will remember you.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: That's not a good thing.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I thought it through, and I decided to do this.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Your brother told me that this country's thorns are what brings him joy.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: What about you? What do you think?
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Hermano thought really, really hard about Bolívar.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: At first, I wanted to be like him, but then I found out I can't do that.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I want more people that I can call family, who will stay by my side forever.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Even if you will not be related by blood?
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Even though we are not related by blood, I will always be my hermano's sister.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I will always be Papá's daughter.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: If they don't want to leave, then I don't think I should leave, either.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: It's that simple.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: You remind me of back when I took over the city.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: My father was a scumbag. This city is a mess that he left to me to sort out.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: I had the ability to change it, but why should I have?
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Tell me, why?
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Because you're your papá's daughter?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: It's not that simple, but it's also not that complicated.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: I don't understand.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: You will, one day.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Now go, mija.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: You are a feather lifted off the ground by a fierce wind. The wind will destroy you without mercy... but if you are tenacious enough, you will see sights that you can see only in the storm.
attributes.name: Candela

attributes.content: Guapa, you know the store's not going to open. What are you doing spacing out here?
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: Who are you?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: I talked to you before. You forgot?
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: I did.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Alright...
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: Here, this is for you.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: Hmm?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Didn't you catch a thief before? The owner wanted to give you a reward, but couldn't find you. So it falls to me.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: I had no idea where you were, but I figured that if you knew so much about this place, you might come back, so I held onto it for you.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: Oh, you're the one who talked to me the other day.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: That's what I just said!
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: What are you doing here?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: My flower shop is just nearby.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: A flower shop?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Yes, I used to be an athlete. I was in the Championship.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: One day, I fell in the arena. Just as everyone was booing me on the ground, I saw a flower, like it was smiling at me.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: So I left the sports world, and opened this shop.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: Eh, wait!
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: ...Do you have any lilacs?
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Of course.
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: I want a bundle of them.
attributes.name: La Pluma

attributes.content: Are they for someone?
attributes.name: Flower Shop Owner

attributes.content: Si. For my family.
attributes.name: La Pluma
